column1: 1 Born and educated in Russia, she moved to the United States in 1926. After two early novels that were initially
unsuccessful and two Broadway plays, Rand achieved fame with her 1943 novel The Fountainhead. In 1957, she
published her best-selling work, the novel Atlas Shrugged. Afterward, until her death in 1982, she turned to non-
fiction to promote her philosophy, publishing her own periodicals and releasing several collections of essays.
